summary: This module provides an inbound and outbound JWT authentication provider, which can be used to authenticate using a JWT and the functionality related to issuing and validating JWT.
description:
Module Overview

This module provides an inbound and outbound JWT authentication provider, which can be used to authenticate using a JWT and the functionality related to issuing and validating JWT.

For information on the operations, which you can perform with this module, see the below Functions. For examples on the usage of the operations, see the following.

  • JWT Issue/Validate Example
  • Secured Client with JWT Auth Example
  • Secured Service with JWT Auth Example

fields.name: clientConfig
fields.description: HTTP client configurations which calls the JWKs endpoint

fields.name: cty
fields.description: Content type, convey structural information about the JWT

fields.name: kid
fields.description: Key ID, hint indicating which key was used to secure the JWS

fields.name: keyStore
fields.description: Keystore to be used in JWT signing

fields.name: iss
fields.description: Issuer, identifies the principal that issued the JWT

fields.name: sub
fields.description: Subject, identifies the principal that is the subject of the JWT

fields.name: aud
fields.description: Audience, identifies the recipients that the JWT is intended for

fields.name: jti
fields.description: JWT ID, unique identifier for the JWT

fields.name: exp
fields.description: Expiration time, identifies the expiration time (seconds since the Epoch) on or after which the JWT must not be accepted

fields.name: nbf
fields.description: Not before, identifies the time (seconds since the Epoch) before which the JWT must not be accepted

fields.name: iat
fields.description: Issued at, identifies the time (seconds since the Epoch) at which the JWT was issued

fields.name: jwtCache
fields.description: Cache used to store parsed JWT information

objects.name: InboundJwtAuthProvider
objects.description:
Represents the inbound JWT auth provider, which authenticates by validating a JWT. The jwt:InboundJwtAuthProvider is another implementation of the auth:InboundAuthProvider interface.

 jwt:InboundJwtAuthProvider inboundJwtAuthProvider = new({
     issuer: "example",
     audience: "ballerina",
     trustStoreConfig: {
         certificateAlias: "ballerina",
         trustStore: {
             path: "/path/to/truststore.p12",
             password: "ballerina"
         }
     }
 });

objects.name: OutboundJwtAuthProvider
objects.description:
Represents the outbound JWT auth provider, which is used to authenticate with an external endpoint by generating a JWT. The jwt:OutboundJwtAuthProvider is another implementation of the auth:OutboundAuthProvider interface.

 jwt:OutboundJwtAuthProvider jwtAuthProvider = new({
     issuer: "example",
     audience: ["ballerina"],
     keyStoreConfig: {
         keyAlias: "ballerina",
         keyPassword: "ballerina",
         keyStore: {
             path: "/path/to/keystore.p12",
             password: "ballerina"
         }
     }
 });

parameters.name: header
parameters.description: JWT header record to be built as a string

returnParameters.description: The header string or else a jwt:Error if building the string fails

functions.name: buildHeaderString
functions.description:
Builds the header string from the jwt:JwtHeader record.

 string|jwt:Error jwtHeader = buildHeaderString(header);

parameters.name: payload
parameters.description: JWT payload record to be built as a string

returnParameters.description: The payload string or else a jwt:Error if building the string fails

functions.name: buildPayloadString
functions.description:
Builds the payload string from the jwt:JwtPayload record.

 string|jwt:Error jwtPayload = jwt:buildPayloadString(payload);

returnParameters.description: The JWT header and payload tuple or else a jwt:Error if token decoding fails

functions.name: decodeJwt
functions.description:
Decodes the given JWT string.

 [jwt:JwtHeader, jwt:JwtPayload]|jwt:Error [header, payload] = jwt:decodeJwt(jwt);

returnParameters.description: JWT as a string or else a jwt:Error if token validation fails

functions.name: issueJwt
functions.description:
Issues a JWT based on the provided header and payload. JWT will be signed (JWS) if crypto:KeyStore information is provided in the jwt:JwtKeyStoreConfig and the alg field of the jwt:JwtHeader is not jwt:NONE.

 string|jwt:Error jwt = jwt:issueJwt(header, payload, keyStoreConfig);

returnParameters.description: JWT payload or else a jwt:Error if token validation fails

functions.name: validateJwt
functions.description:
Validates the given JWT string.

 jwt:JwtPayload|jwt:Error result = jwt:validateJwt(jwt, validatorConfig);

unionTypes.name: Error
unionTypes.description: Represents the JWT error type with details. This will be returned if an error occurred while issuing/validating a JWT or any operation related to JWT.

unionTypes.name: JwtSigningAlgorithm
unionTypes.description: The key algorithms supported by crypto module.
